  "body": "You can look through conversation in Discord design channel starting from this message https://discord.com/channels/624634427930312714/928625369542713396/1120694411441995807\r\n\r\n## Problem \r\nCurrently we never show unread badge for 1-1/group chats. We show unread counters for all all kinds of messages. \r\n\r\nAt the same time, Messages bottom tab still shows counter only in case of unread replies/mentions and shows unread badge for rest of messages. \r\n\r\nIt causes wrong total number of counters shown on Messages tab. \r\n\r\n**Steps:**\r\n\r\n1. Alice sends Bob 1 mention and 1 ordinary messages in 1-1 chat. \r\n\r\n**Actual result:** Bob observes counter 2 on 1-1 chat but counter 1 on Messages tab (screenshot attached). \r\n\r\n![photo_2023-06-20_15 38 59](https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/97245802/e12ca345-fad6-451b-89c4-bf233066e728)\r\n\r\n**Expected result:** \r\n\r\nThe Messages  bottom tab should display “2” as the number displayed here should always be the sum of all the individual counters in that section of the app\r\n\r\n\r\n- Status version: nightly \r\n- Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
